Two women&nbsp;aged 25 and 58 were issued with fines of R1 000 each for offences relating to the liquor act and a&nbsp;25-year-old man was detained for possession of dagga and selling beer concoctions&nbsp;during the Joza SAPS&#39;s pre Easter Operations&nbsp;tis afternoon. The team yielded&nbsp;200 litres of home-brewed concoction; 15 beer crates and 225 empty one-litre bottles&nbsp;and&nbsp;2kg of brown sugar used to make the concoction. In addition, two&nbsp;illegal sheebens were raided and alcohol confiscated. The 25-year-old man&nbsp;will appear in the Magistrate&#39;s Court in Grahamstown soon.